---
import { getEntry } from 'astro:content';

import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
import PageHeader from '../components/layout/PageHeader.astro';
import SponsorLogo from '../components/layout/SponsorLogo.astro';
import Button from '../components/ui/Button.astro';
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

import Segment from '@/components/layout/Segment.astro';
import Headline from '@/components/ui/typography/Headline.astro';
import Paragraph from '@/components/ui/typography/Paragraph.astro';
import Link from '@/components/util/Link.astro';
import Divider from '../components/layout/Divider.astro';
import InlineSVG from '../components/util/InlineSVG.astro';

const sponsors = await getEntry('sponsors', 'info');
const tiers = await getEntry('sponsors', 'tiers');
---

<Layout title="Backing">
    <PageHeader text="Backing" />
    <Segment variant="white" container yPadding class="py-4 md:py-0 mb-8">
        <Headline level={2} variant="blue"
            >How to back the project financially?</Headline
        >
        <Paragraph size="lg" class="mt-2">
            While NixOS is free and open-source, there are a lot of costs coming
            with such a large project. Your support helps us keep it
            sustainable. There are two main ways to support the project:
        </Paragraph>
        <div class="grid gap-8 pt-4 md:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
                <div
                    class="bg-secondary-afghani-blue-95 flex flex-col gap-2 rounded-2xl p-4"
                >
                    <Headline level={3} variant="blue"> Sponsorships </Headline>
                    <Paragraph size="lg">
                        Recurring support with perks in return.
                    </Paragraph>
                    <Paragraph>
                        Help us keep NixOS and Nixpkgs sustainable by becoming a
                        sponsor. Your support helps us maintain the
                        infrastructure, improve the project, and organize
                        events. We offer various sponsorship tiers, each with
                        its own set of benefits.
                    </Paragraph>
                    <Paragraph class="font-semibold">
                        Ideal for organizations and businesses who want to make
                        a long-term commitment to the project.
                    </Paragraph>
                    <Button
                        color="semidarkblue"
                        size="sm"
                        href="/sponsorship"
                        classList={['mt-1']}
                    >
                        Read more about Sponsorships
                    </Button>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col">
                <div
                    class="bg-secondary-afghani-blue-95 flex flex-col gap-2 rounded-2xl p-4"
                >
                    <Headline level={3} variant="blue"> Donations </Headline>
                    <Paragraph size="lg">
                        Simple one-time or recurring payments.
                    </Paragraph>
                    <Paragraph>
                        Show your support by donating to the NixOS Foundation.
                        This helps us continue to provide free, open-source
                        software to the community. This is a regular donation
                        with no perks in return. We accept donations either via
                        Open Collective or via bank transfer.
                    </Paragraph>
                    <Paragraph class="font-semibold">
                        Ideal for individuals and organizations who want to just
                        say thank you and secure the projects future.
                    </Paragraph>
                    <Button
                        color="semidarkblue"
                        size="sm"
                        href="/sponsorship"
                        classList={['mt-1']}
                    >
                        Read more about Ways to Donate
                    </Button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </Segment>
    <Divider style="slope" mirrorY />
    <Segment variant="blue" container yPadding innerClass="py-4 md:py-0">
        <Headline level={3} variant="white">Sponsorship Tiers</Headline>
        <Paragraph variant="white" size="lg" class="mt-2 mb-2">
            We offer a variety of sponsorship tiers to support NixOS
            development.
        </Paragraph>
        <ul class="grid md:grid-cols-4 mb-4 gap-4 md:gap-0">
            {
                tiers.data.map((tier) => (
                    <li class="group flex flex-col justify-between">
                        <div class="flex flex-1 flex-col">
                            <h4 class="bg-secondary-afghani-blue-25 text-primary-white flex items-center justify-between rounded-t-xl p-2 text-lg font-bold md:rounded-t-none md:group-first:rounded-tl-xl md:group-last:rounded-tr-xl">
                                {tier.name}{' '}
                                <span class="bg-secondary-afghani-blue-15 rounded-xl px-2 py-1 text-base">
                                    {tier.contribution}
                                </span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="bg-secondary-afghani-blue-35 flex-1 py-1">
                                {tier.benefits.map((benefit) => (
                                    <li class="border-b-secondary-afghani-blue-45 inline-flex w-full items-center gap-2 border-b-1 p-2 last:border-b-0 md:min-h-16">
                                        <Icon
                                            name={benefit.icon}
                                            class="text-secondary-afghani-blue-85 min-h-5 min-w-5"
                                        />{' '}
                                        {benefit.description}
                                    </li>
                                ))}
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        {tier.requirements && (
                            <p class="bg-secondary-afghani-blue-35 text-primary-white px-2 py-1 text-sm">
                                {tier.requirements}
                            </p>
                        )}
                        <Button
                            color="semidarkblue"
                            classList={[
                                'rounded-none rounded-b-xl md:rounded-b-none md:group-first:rounded-bl-xl md:group-last:rounded-br-xl',
                                'bg-secondary-afghani-blue-25!',
                            ]}
                            href="mailto:foundation@nixos.org"
                        >
                            Get in touch
                        </Button>
                    </li>
                ))
            }
        </ul>
        <Headline level={4} variant="white"
            >Are you a university or startup?</Headline
        >
        <Paragraph size="lg" variant="white" class="mt-2">
            We are aware that many universities and startups are interested in
            supporting NixOS but may struggle with the finincial entrylevel. Get
            in touch with us to learn about our community tier which will grant
            you a logo on our website.
        </Paragraph>
    </Segment>
    <Segment variant="blue" container yPadding innerClass="py-4 md:py-0">
        <Headline level={3} variant="white">Ways to donate</Headline>
        <Paragraph size="lg" class="mt-4" />
        <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
            <div
                class="bg-secondary-afghani-blue-35 flex flex-col gap-2 rounded-2xl p-4"
            >
                <Headline level={3} variant="white">Open Collective</Headline>
                <Paragraph variant="white">
                    NixOS Foundation is using
                    <Link variant="white" href="https://opencollective.com/"
                        >Open Collective</Link
                    >
                    to manage the finances so everyone can see where money comes from
                    and where money goes.
                </Paragraph>
                <Paragraph variant="white">
                    With Open Collective you can make a <strong>single</strong> or
                    <strong>recurring</strong> contribution by credit card transfer.
                </Paragraph>
                <Button
                    color="semidarkblue"
                    classList={['mt-1']}
                    size="sm"
                    href="https://opencollective.com/nixos#support"
                >
                    Donate using Open Collective
                </Button>
            </div>

            <div
                class="bg-secondary-afghani-blue-35 flex flex-col gap-2 rounded-2xl p-4"
            >
                <Headline level={3} variant="white"
                    >SEPA Bank Transfer*</Headline
                >
                <pre
                    class="bg-secondary-afghani-blue-25 text-nix-blue-darker my-2 rounded-3xl p-8 font-mono font-bold whitespace-pre-line">
    Stichting NixOS Foundation, Utrecht, The Netherlands

    IBAN: NL13 BUNQ 2061 2530 32
    BIC:  BUNQNL2AXXX</pre>
            </div>
        </div>
        <Paragraph size="sm" variant="white" class="col-span-2 mt-2">
            * Please add your name and purpose (donation) in the description of
            the transfer.
            <i>
                If you would like to support us with amounts above 2000 euro per
                year, please contact us at
                <Link variant="white" href="mailto:foundation@nixos.org"
                    >foundation@nixos.org</Link
                >
                , as this will have tax implications.
            </i>
        </Paragraph>
    </Segment>
    <Divider style="slope" mirrorX />
    <Segment
        variant="white"
        container
        yPadding
        innerClass="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2 py-4 md:py-0"
    >
        <div class="flex flex-col justify-center gap-4 leading-relaxed">
            <Headline level={2} variant="blue"> The NixOS Foundation </Headline>
            <Paragraph variant="black" size="lg">
                The NixOS infrastructure, development and events are funded by
                its users and sponsors.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph variant="black">
                Maintaining our build farm and binary cache is very expensive.
                We depend on your support to ensure the continuous operation and
                expansion of the NixOS infrastructure.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph variant="black">
                Please consider donating a small amount every month to
                contribute to sustainable funding. Donations are handled by a
                nonprofit organization, the <Link
                    variant="blue"
                    href="/community#foundation">NixOS Foundation</Link
                >.
            </Paragraph>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center">
            <InlineSVG
                src="/src/assets/image/nixos-foundation-logo.svg"
                class="max-h-96"
            />
        </div>
    </Segment>

    <Divider style="slope" mirrorY />
    <Segment
        variant="blue"
        container
        yPadding
        innerClass="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2 py-4 md:py-0"
    >
        <div class="flex flex-col justify-center">
            <div
                class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 xl:grid-cols-4"
            >
                {
                    sponsors.data.items.map((item) => (
                        <SponsorLogo
                            class={item.class}
                            href={item.href}
                            src={item.src}
                            alt={item.alt}
                        />
                    ))
                }
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col justify-center gap-4">
            <Headline level={2} variant="white">Acknowledgements</Headline>
            <Paragraph variant="white">
                The Nix package manager was developed by
                <Link variant="white" href="https://edolstra.github.io/"
                    >Eelco Dolstra</Link
                >
                as part of his PhD research in the
                <Link
                    variant="white"
                    href="https://www.nwo.nl/en/projects/638001201"
                    >TraCE project</Link
                >, funded by the
                <Link variant="white" href="http://www.jacquard.nl/"
                    >Jacquard programme</Link
                >
                of the
                <Link variant="white" href="http://www.nwo.npx-l/"
                    >Netherlands Organisation for Scientific Research</Link
                >
                (NWO) and SERC. The first prototype of NixOS was developed by
                <Link variant="white" href="http://www.tjaldur.nl/"
                    >Armijn Hemel</Link
                >
                as his master’s thesis project. Hydra, the Nix-based continuous build
                system, was developed as part of the LaQuSo Buildfarm project, funded
                by
                <Link variant="white" href="https://www.4tu.nl/nirict/"
                    >NIRICT</Link
                >
                and
                <Link variant="white" href="http://www.laquso.com/">LaQuSo</Link
                >.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph variant="white">
                The following companies and institutes have supported the
                development of NixOS and hosting for its infrastructure. We are
                very grateful for that! If you would like to support us as well,
                please contact
                <Link variant="white" href="mailto:foundation@nixos.org"
                    >The NixOS Foundation</Link
                >.
            </Paragraph>
        </div>
    </Segment>
</Layout>
